entries.title: Zoom to Lay Off 1,300 Workers, Joining Other Tech Giants
entries.description: The company is cutting 15 percent of its work force, or about 1,300 jobs, citing “the uncertainty of the global economy.”

entries.title: Ex-Coinbase Employee Pleads Guilty to Insider Trading
entries.description: The case was part of a crackdown on an old-school financial crime in the crypto world.

entries.title: Microsoft Launches an A.I.-Powered Bing
entries.description: Amid the tech industry’s worst slump in decades, industry leaders are predicting an era built on new chatbots and other types of artificial intelligence.

entries.title: Few Americans Understand Online Privacy and Tracking, Report Says
entries.description: Many consumers want control over their personal details. But few understand how online tracking works, says a new report from the University of Pennsylvania.

entries.title: Americans Flunked This Test on Online Privacy
entries.description: Many consumers want control over their personal details. But few understand how online tracking works, says a new report from the University of Pennsylvania.

entries.title: Meta, Long an AI Leader, Tries Not to Be Left Out of the Boom
entries.description: It has long had technology to rival chatbots like ChatGPT, but can’t afford to back artificial intelligence that can spread misinformation and toxic content.
